EXTRACTED VALUE: Drive, crash, mini-game, repeat. Pimp My Ride is a licensed game for die-hard fans.
As a whole the game feels undercooked, unpolished and ultimately unsatisfying.
Sadly, the game's not much fun - you get bored easily and there's not much variety to be had waving your arms up and down. [Dec 2006, p.99]
The main difference between this and Pokemon is that Pokemon doesn't suck as much. Game play in Digimon World 2 is the equivalent of a snail race.
Run about? No. Run far, far away.
It requires you to work too much to accomplish the objectives, and for too little reward.
I have seen NES games that look better than this game.
Just don't play that bloody enhanced version, you'll never forgive yourself. [Issue#29, p.118]
In total, the whole Basic Training experience lives up to the 'basic' in the title, and will take you an hour to complete.
